=== STEP: ask-endpoints ===
--- cmd: bny brane ask what API endpoints do we need for a complete RSVP system? ---
asking brane...
# API Endpoints for a Complete RSVP System

## Core RSVP Operations

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `POST` | `/events/:id/rsvps` | Create RSVP (system determines accepted vs waitlisted) |
| `GET` | `/events/:id/rsvps` | List attendees (filtered by status, paginated, visibility-scoped) |
| `GET` | `/rsvps/:id` | Get single RSVP detail |
| `PATCH` | `/rsvps/:id` | Update RSVP (change party_size, note, notification preference) |
| `DELETE` | `/rsvps/:id` | Cancel RSVP (returns `undo_token` + `undo_expires_at`) |
| `POST` | `/rsvps/:id/undo` | Undo cancellation within grace window (`?token=xxx`) |
| `POST` | `/rsvps/:id/confirm` | Confirm promotion from waitlist (accepts the `promoted` state) |

Key design: `POST /events/:id/rsvps` never accepts a `status` parameter. The server determines accepted vs waitlisted based on capacity. Waitlisting returns `201 Created` with `status: waitlisted`, not an error.

## Event Management

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `POST` | `/events` | Create event |
| `GET` | `/events` | List events (with filters: geo, temporal, capacity, category) |
| `GET` | `/events/:id` | Get event detail (includes `spots_remaining`, lifecycle phase) |
| `PATCH` | `/events/:id` | Update event (time, location, capacity — capacity reduction triggers special flow) |
| `DELETE` | `/events/:id` | Cancel event (destructive — requires confirmation pattern) |
| `POST` | `/events/:id/clone` | Duplicate event for recurring/repeat use |

## Organizer Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `PATCH` | `/events/:id/rsvps/:rsvp_id` | Organizer override: manually accept/decline/waitlist a user |
| `POST` | `/events/:id/actions/promote-all` | Async bulk promotion (returns job ID) |
| `POST` | `/events/:id/actions/message` | Message all or filtered attendees |
| `GET` | `/events/:id/rsvps/export` | Export attendee list (CSV/PDF) |
| `GET` | `/events/:id/analytics` | RSVP conversion, no-show rate, cancellation patterns |
| `POST` | `/events/:id/rsvps/:rsvp_id/no-show` | Mark no-show post-event |

### Capacity Reduction Flow
`PATCH /events/:id` with reduced capacity should:
1. Return a preview of affected RSVPs before confirming
2. Require explicit confirmation parameter
3. Record `capacity_change` reason in audit trail

## User Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `GET` | `/users/me/rsvps` | My RSVPs across all events |
| `GET` | `/users/me/events` | Events I'm attending |
| `PATCH` | `/users/me` | Update profile, notification preferences |
| `DELETE` | `/users/me` | Account deletion (soft delete, GDPR cascade) |

## Webhooks & Real-Time

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `POST` | `/webhooks` | Register webhook (event types: rsvp.created, capacity.reached, event.cancelled) |
| `GET` | `/webhooks` | List registered webhooks |
| `DELETE` | `/webhooks/:id` | Remove webhook |
| `GET` | `/events/:id/stream` | SSE endpoint for live capacity updates (or ActionCable channel) |

## Discovery (Platform-Level, Optional)

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `GET` | `/events/search` | Full-text + geo + temporal + social search |
| `GET` | `/events/trending` | Popular events |
| `GET` | `/events/recommended` | Personalized recommendations (opt-in only) |
| `GET` | `/events?similar_to=:id` | Similar events |

## Supporting Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `GET` | `/events/:id/waitlist` | Waitlist position and count (privacy-scoped) |
| `POST` | `/batch` | Batch operations envelope (multiple actions in one request) |
| `GET` | `/jobs/:id` | Poll async job status (for bulk operations) |

## Idempotency Notes

- `POST /events/:id/rsvps` is naturally idempotent via `(user_id, event_id)` unique constraint — second POST returns `200` with existing RSVP
- Support `Idempotency-Key` header for non-naturally-idempotent mutations
- All responses include `Retry-After` on 429/503

## Progressive Disclosure

Level 1 (minimal): `POST /events/:id/rsvps` with empty body — just works.
Level 2 (options): Add `party_size`, `note`.
Level 3 (power): Add `idempotency_key`, `notification_preference`, webhook callbacks.

## What's Missing (Open Questions)

- **Recurring events**: Series-level RSVP endpoints (`POST /series/:id/rsvps`?) depend on whether series is a first-class entity
- **Payments/deposits**: Would add `/events/:id/rsvps/:id/payment` and saga orchestration
- **Multi-organizer RBAC**: Permission management endpoints for organizer roles

